	<h level="2">1. Create .gitignore</h>
	<code language="text"><![CDATA[
# Angular / Node
node_modules/
dist/
tmp/
temp/
.angular/
.cache/

# IDE / Editor
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# Logs & Reports
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
coverage/
*.lcov

# Environment / Secrets
.env
.env.*

# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Misc
*.tsbuildinfo
/.husky/_/
]]></code>

	<h level="2">2. Initialize Git Repository and Create Remote (GitHub CLI)</h>
	<code language="bash"><![CDATA[
# Initialize if not already
git init

# Add MIT License (gh can do this automatically on repo creation, but include file first if desired)
cat > LICENSE <<'EOF'
MIT License

Copyright (c) 2025 HERE AND NOW AI

Permission is hereby granted, free of charge, to any person obtaining a copy
