EOF

git add .
git commit -m "chore: initial commit (About Us Angular app)"
git branch -M main

# Create GitHub repo (requires authenticated gh CLI)
gh repo create hereandnowai/aboutus --public --source=. --remote=origin --push --license MIT --description "Angular About Us site for HERE AND NOW AI"

# If repo already exists, just add remote & push
# git remote add origin git@github.com:hereandnowai/aboutus.git || true
# git push -u origin main
]]></code>

	<h level="2">3. Add GitHub Secrets (Required for FTP Deploy)</h>
	<p>In the GitHub repo settings, add the following secrets (Settings &gt; Secrets and variables &gt; Actions):</p>
	<code language="text"><![CDATA[
FTP_HOST=hexagonkomputers.in
FTP_USERNAME=hereanda
FTP_PASSWORD=__REPLACE_WITH_SECURE_PASSWORD__
FTP_TARGET_DIR=/apps.hereandnowai.com/apps/aboutus
]]></code>

	<h level="2">4. GitHub Actions Workflow (.github/workflows/deploy.yml)</h>
	<code language="yaml"><![CDATA[
name: CI Build & FTP Deploy

on:
	push:
		branches: [ "main" ]
	workflow_dispatch:

jobs:
	build-and-deploy:
		runs-on: ubuntu-latest
		steps:
			- name: Checkout
				uses: actions/checkout@v4
			- name: Use Node.js 20
				uses: actions/setup-node@v4
				with:
					node-version: 20
					cache: npm
			- name: Install dependencies
				run: npm ci
			- name: Build
				run: npm run build --if-present
			- name: Debug dist
				run: ls -R dist || true
			- name: FTP Deploy
				uses: SamKirkland/FTP-Deploy-Action@v4
				with:
					server: ${{ secrets.FTP_HOST }}
					username: ${{ secrets.FTP_USERNAME }}
					password: ${{ secrets.FTP_PASSWORD }}
					server-dir: ${{ secrets.FTP_TARGET_DIR }}/
					local-dir: dist/aboutus/
					dangerous-clean-slate: true
					exclude: |
						**/.git*
						**/.github/**
						node_modules/**
]]></code>

	<h level="2">5. Deployment Flow</h>
	<p>Push to main triggers build, then FTP deploy uploads the built assets in dist/aboutus to the target directory.</p>

	<h level="2">6. Notes</h>
	<p>Store all credentials only as GitHub Secrets (no plaintext). Review workflow for potential SFTP upgrade if supported by server. Remove dangerous-clean-slate for incremental deploys.</p>
</poml>
